
# Before attempting to play have reequired tooling installed on local system:

1. git 
1. nodejs
1. npm
1. vite deploy tool

# Play the game on local system multi-client in browser configure the development server to listen on all network interfaces and then access it using your computer's local IP address for multi device LAN play


1. locate your network IP on windows 
    - command prompt `ipconfig`
    - look for the IPv4 Address under your active network connection be it `wifi` or `ethernet adapter`

1. run vite development with the host flag 
    - `npm vite --host`

1. From your internet browser enter in the network address from the console on any local internet connected device
    
# Play the game on local system multi-client in browser

clone repo

In the project root run commands :

```
    npm i

    npx vite build
```

# In the project /server run command:

```
node index.js

```

## for local single-player development start the server with command

```
npx vite
```



## to deploy new changes: 

create a new branch off of the deploy ready staging branch.
in the deploy-branch update the bundled code by running the command:
npm run build

then :
 change the vite.config.js to match with the deploy config linked in this section

make a pull request again the branch to be deployed with the new bundled code 
deploy the new code to gh-pages by the pages panel, click deplyed and re-run all jobs on the next page.

config for deploy: 
https://github.com/Dominique-Sakrisson/ace-altitude/blob/main/vite.config.js



